There are many photos of prisoners of war and the dead circulating on social media. Please don’t share them.

@ICRC will explain that the Geneva Protocols forbid the use of the images of POWs. And the dead have lost enough already.

This is Putin’s war.

@IlvesToomas I make that point too. This is a decision we must all make but let's not pretend we don't have a stake in this. Putin and his allies have shown that we already do.

You may not want to fight, but others get to choose if you have to.
https://t.co/NqZY8sYNJ5

For many of us, the news from Afghanistan is more than just images and tales. It’s the seared memory of pain and loss.

It’s essential that we hear the truth of what’s happening, how that is reported matters.

@HelpforHeroes has set out some areas to consider. https://t.co/oHxgtYD9Ah

Happy 30th anniversary of the restoration of your freedom from all in 🇬🇧, @markomihkelson 🇪🇪
